Package com.lucaslouca.commands

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    LLCommand
    Interface defining a command that can be executed.
    LLCommandFactory
    Interface that defines which functionality an LLCommand factory must provide.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    LLAbstractRailRoadServiceCommand
    Abstract class defining an LLCommand related to the LLRailRoadService functionality.
    LLAbstractStartDestinationCommand
    LLAbstractRailRoadServiceCommand that computes the number of possible routes starting from start and ending at dest.
    LLCommandProccesor
    Class that processes LLCommand commands.
    LLCountRoutesWithHopsCommand
    LLAbstractStartDestinationCommand that computes the number of possible routes starting from start and ending at dest with an exact number of stops.
    LLCountRoutesWithMaxDistanceCommand
    LLAbstractStartDestinationCommand that computes the number of possible routes starting from start and ending at dest with a maximum distance.
    LLCountRoutesWithMaxHopsCommand
    LLAbstractStartDestinationCommand that computes the number of possible routes starting from start and ending at dest with a maximum number of stops.
    LLDistanceCommand
    LLAbstractRailRoadServiceCommand that computes the distance of a route.
    LLRailRoadServiceCommandFactory
    This class implements the LLCommandFactory Interface.
    LLShortestPathCommand
    {code LLAbstractStartDestinationCommand} that computes the shortest path between two towns.
    LLShortestPathLengthCommand
    {code LLAbstractStartDestinationCommand} that computes the length of the shortest path between two towns.
